metadata.name: You talkin' to me?
metadata.description:
Tarpons are for me one of the wonders of Bonaire, an island in the Netherlands Caribbean. They are large fish that measure up to 2 m (8 ft) long and can weight up to 120 Kg (265 lb) Despite their imposing size they are very curious and friendly; You are never alone when diving with them.

During the day they aren't very active and relatively few are seen, but at night they star a special show: the hunt.

Diving with a group of tarpons at night is a unique experience. They will use the diver's lights as target-lights to pinpoint their preys to quickly eat them, with a low and sudden noise.

They'll get so close to you that they will actually push you aside hard. Is in that moment you thank that tarpons are not aggressive!
